com.beaglebuddy.mp3.id3v23
Class ID3v23FrameHeader

java.lang.Object
  com.beaglebuddy.mp3.id3v23.ID3v23FrameHeader

public class ID3v23FrameHeader
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides methods for reading and writing frame headers in ID3V2.3 frames. A frame header is 10 bytes long and precedes the frame body in an ID3v2.3 frame. A frame header has the following fields:

Frame Header Fields
 FieldDescription
1. id 4 character type identifier of the frame
2. padding
3. frameBodySize
4. tagAlterPreservation
5. fileAlterPreservation
6. readOnly
7. compressed
8. encrypted
9. belongsToGroup
10.uncompressedSize
8. encryptionMethod
9. groupId
10.dirty

See Also:
ID3 tag version 2.3.0 standard, wikipedia history of ID3 tags

Constructor Detail

ID3v23FrameHeader

public ID3v23FrameHeader(FrameType frameType)
This constructor is called when creating a new frame header. The default values used are:
  • frame body size is 0
  • tag alter preservation is false
  • file alter preservation is false
  • read only is false
  • compressed is false
  • encrypted is false
  • belongs to a group is false

Parameters:
frameType - ID3v2.3 frame type.

setBuffer

public void setBuffer()
if the frame header's values have been modified, then resize the raw binary buffer and store the new values there. When finished, the dirty flag is reset to indicate that the buffer is up to date, and the frame is now ready to be saved to the .mp3 file.
